title: MiniMap
content:
local function initializeMiniMap()
    local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
    local screenGui = player:WaitForChild("PlayerGui"):FindFirstChild("MiniMapGui") or Instance.new("ScreenGui", player.PlayerGui)
    screenGui.Name = "MiniMapGui"

    -- Mini-map frame
    local miniMapFrame = screenGui:FindFirstChild("MiniMapFrame") or Instance.new("Frame", screenGui)
    miniMapFrame.Name = "MiniMapFrame"
    miniMapFrame.Size = UDim2.new(0, 200, 0, 200) -- Initial size
    miniMapFrame.Position = UDim2.new(0, 10, 0, 10) -- Position the mini-map on the screen
    miniMapFrame.BackgroundColor3 = Color3.fromRGB(0, 0, 0)
    miniMapFrame.BackgroundTransparency = 0.5
    miniMapFrame.ClipsDescendants = true

    -- Range input box
    local rangeInput = screenGui:FindFirstChild("RangeInput") or Instance.new("TextBox", screenGui)
    rangeInput.Name = "RangeInput"
    rangeInput.Size = UDim2.new(0, 100, 0, 50)
    rangeInput.Position = UDim2.new(1, -110, 0, 10) -- Position on the right side of the screen
    rangeInput.PlaceholderText = "Enter range"
    rangeInput.Text = ""
    rangeInput.BackgroundColor3 = Color3.fromRGB(255, 255, 255)
    rangeInput.TextColor3 = Color3.fromRGB(0, 0, 0)

    -- Size input box
    local sizeInput = screenGui:FindFirstChild("SizeInput") or Instance.new("TextBox", screenGui)
    sizeInput.Name = "SizeInput"
    sizeInput.Size = UDim2.new(0, 100, 0, 50)
    sizeInput.Position = UDim2.new(1, -110, 0, 70) -- Position below the range input
    sizeInput.PlaceholderText = "Enter size"
    sizeInput.Text = ""
    sizeInput.BackgroundColor3 = Color3.fromRGB(255, 255, 255)
    sizeInput.TextColor3 = Color3.fromRGB(0, 0, 0)

    local viewSize = 50
    local scaleFactor = miniMapFrame.Size.X.Offset / viewSize

    -- Update mini-map
    local function updateMiniMap()
        local character = player.Character
        if not character or not character:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart") then return end
        local hrp = character.HumanoidRootPart
        local viewCenter = hrp.Position

        -- Clear previous mini-map elements
        for _, child in ipairs(miniMapFrame:GetChildren()) do
            if child:IsA("Frame") then
                child:Destroy()
            end
        end

        -- Update parts on mini-map
        local partsInView = workspace:FindPartsInRegion3(Region3.new(
            viewCenter - Vector3.new(viewSize/2, 0, viewSize/2),
            viewCenter + Vector3.new(viewSize/2, 0, viewSize/2)
        ), nil, math.huge)
        
        for _, part in ipairs(partsInView) do
            if part:IsA("BasePart") then
                local partGui = Instance.new("Frame", miniMapFrame)
                local partSize = part.Size * scaleFactor
                partGui.Size = UDim2.new(0, partSize.X, 0, partSize.Z) -- Size of each part's GUI representation based on part size
                partGui.BackgroundColor3 = part.BrickColor.Color
                local partPos = (part.Position - viewCenter) * scaleFactor
                partGui.Position = UDim2.new(0, partPos.X + miniMapFrame.Size.X.Offset/2 - partSize.X/2, 0, partPos.Z + miniMapFrame.Size.Y.Offset/2 - partSize.Z/2) -- Center the box
                partGui.Visible = (part.Position - viewCenter).Magnitude <= viewSize/2
            end
        end
    end

    -- Update mini-map every frame
    game:GetService("RunService").RenderStepped:Connect(updateMiniMap)

    -- Change view range based on input
    rangeInput.FocusLost:Connect(function(enterPressed)
        if enterPressed then
            local newRange = tonumber(rangeInput.Text)
            if newRange then
                viewSize = newRange
                scaleFactor = miniMapFrame.Size.X.Offset / viewSize
            else
                rangeInput.Text = tostring(viewSize) -- Reset to current view size if input is invalid
            end
        end
    end)

    -- Change mini-map size based on input
    sizeInput.FocusLost:Connect(function(enterPressed)
        if enterPressed then
            local newSize = tonumber(sizeInput.Text)
            if newSize then
                miniMapFrame.Size = UDim2.new(0, newSize, 0, newSize)
                scaleFactor = newSize / viewSize
            else
                sizeInput.Text = tostring(miniMapFrame.Size.X.Offset) -- Reset to current size if input is invalid
            end
        end
    end)
end

-- Ensure the script re-executes on respawn
local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer

player.CharacterAdded:Connect(function()
    wait(1) -- Give time for the character to load
    initializeMiniMap()
end)

-- Wait for the game to fully load before initializing the mini-map
repeat wait() until game:IsLoaded()

-- Initialize mini-map for the first time
initializeMiniMap()
